When Elmo finds out how much they love to read, he can't wait to become a bookaneer himself. Can he pass the test and help them find their treasure? Bert and Ernie are also on the hunt for treasure in an episode from the fantastic new claymation series Bert and Ernie's Great Adventures. Plus, you can sing along with Abby in a song about something she treasures: words! In Elmo's World: Books, Elmo invites you to learn all about the books he treasures. The song is available on Spotify, iTunes, Google Play Music, Deezer and other stores.

About the song:

"A Sailor Went to Sea is a children's nursery rhyme, clapping game and jump-rope rhyme. It was initially called 'My Father Went to Sea', before becoming more widely known as A Sailor Went to Sea. It is typically sung to the tune of The Sailor's Hornpipe."
The song was parodied in an episode of VeggieTales as "Some Veggies Went To Sea".
The song appeared in "Gloriana", episode 10, season 1 of the Netflix drama The Crown.
